<paragraph blockId="25.[826,1442,464,609]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis box="[826,978,465,486]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Known range</emphasis>
: Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1245,1294,464,485]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">type</typeStatus>
locality (but see below). The species has not been collected or reported since its original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Fransen CHJM" box="[1263,1430,525,547]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" pagination="231 - 260" refId="ref65450" refString="Fransen CHJM. 1997. Lebbeus africanus spec. nov., a new shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda, Caridea, Hippolytidae) from Mauritanian waters, with redescriptions of four other species in the genus. Zoologische Mededelingen 71 (20): 231 - 260." type="journal article" year="1997">Fransen, 1997</bibRefCitation>
). The only possible vent occurrence consists of the specimens noted below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[826,1442,633,1176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis box="[826,925,633,654]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Material</emphasis>
: 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="EPR, T, LACM" collectorName="Shank &amp; J. Martin &amp; We &amp; Tim Shank" county="The" location="County" municipality="Natural History Museum of Los" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" specimenCode="CR 1999, 050.1, 051.1" specimenCount="4" stateProvince="Moscow" typeStatus="holotype">
The single 
<typeStatus box="[1070,1167,633,655]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
was the only specimen known to 
<bibRefCitation author="Fransen CHJM" box="[952,1133,663,685]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" pagination="231 - 260" refId="ref65450" refString="Fransen CHJM. 1997. Lebbeus africanus spec. nov., a new shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda, Caridea, Hippolytidae) from Mauritanian waters, with redescriptions of four other species in the genus. Zoologische Mededelingen 71 (20): 231 - 260." type="journal article" year="1997">Fransen (1997)</bibRefCitation>
at the time of his redescription of the species. Fransen referred to the male 
<typeStatus box="[826,923,725,747]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
as having a carapace length of 
<quantity box="[1335,1441,725,747]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.53" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="15.3">15.3 mm</quantity>
and being registered as Ma 4046 (Zoological Museum of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1024,1114,786,807]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Moscow</collectingRegion>
Lomonossov State University). Unpublished collections of shrimp of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WHITE" authorityYear="1847" box="[826,918,847,868]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,918,847,868]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Lebbeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that ‘key’ to this species (based mostly on the length of the rostrum and number of epipods) 
<collectingMethod box="[826,1133,909,931]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">were collected from traps</collectingMethod>
near a vent field in the southern portion of the 
<collectionCode box="[1109,1161,940,961]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">EPR</collectionCode>
(
<collectionCode box="[1180,1197,939,960]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">T</collectionCode>
. 
<collectorName box="[1211,1285,939,961]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Shank</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[1326,1438,939,961]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">J. Martin</collectorName>
, unpubl. data). 
<collectorName box="[997,1032,971,992]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">We</collectorName>
are aware of 
<specimenCount box="[1199,1339,970,992]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" type="generic">4 specimens</specimenCount>
possibly belonging to this species (see below) that were collected in a 
<collectingMethod box="[978,1113,1031,1053]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">baited trap</collectingMethod>
from a vent field on the southern 
<collectionCode box="[938,993,1063,1084]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">EPR</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingCounty box="[1005,1049,1062,1084]" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">The</collectingCounty>
specimens were collected by 
<collectorName pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Tim Shank</collectorName>
and donated to the 
<collectingMunicipality pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Natural History Museum of Los</collectingMunicipality>
<collectingRegion box="[922,1012,1123,1145]" country="Philippines" name="Angeles" pageId="25" pageNumber="470">Angeles</collectingRegion>
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D96F29FFBCFF99FC60FEEFFB0C0BE4:8EAF88E4FFBCFF99FBECFBD8FB8A0A64" box="[1030,1113,1124,1145]" county="The" municipality="Natural History Museum of Los" name="County" pageId="25" pageNumber="470" stateProvince="Moscow">County</location>
